# hardware_node

This node is one of the base nodes in minho_team ROS package, available on team's GitHub for free use. This node allows communication with the centralized hardware controller. Currently the node supports communication for the current sub-modules:

>Send to node: [controlInfo.msg]
- Omni3MD movement commands
- Kick commands for soccer kicker

>Receive from node:[hardwareInfo.msg]
- Omni3MD information (odometry)
- Camera, PC and Main battery voltages
- IMU heading value
- Free-wheel switch state
- Ball sensor value

# Configuration

To configure this node, go to hardware_node/config and edit node.conf file. This file is necessary to allow an easy configuration of parameters to be used [send to node], maximum and minimum values for variables. The configuration has to follow the following structure:

- To comment a line use #
- Start a variable definition by @, like in the following example:

```
#Define the sub modules
@N_SUBMODULES=2
@SUB_MODULE_0 = OMNI
@SUB_MODULE_1 = KICK
#Define the used modules
@USED_MODULES = 0,1
#Define the maximum and minimum limits
#MAX/MIN_[MODULE ID]_[VARIABLE_ID]=VALUE
@MAX_0_0=80
@MIN_0_0=0
@MAX_0_1=80
@MIN_0_1=-80
```
# Current Version
1.1

# Edit log

>Version 1.0 - Basic version supporting only MSL hardware communication, with no configuration procedures.

>Version 1.1 - Configuration procedures added, to include or exclude sub modules and configure maximum and minimum values for certain parameters, provided in node.conf file.

